text: Tamás Pomucz (12 June 1957 - 31 July 2020) was a Hungarian sailor. He competed in the Flying Dutchman event at the 1992 Summer Olympics. He was born in Siófok, Hungary. Pomucz died on 31 July 2020, aged 63. ==References== Category:1957 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Olympians for Hungary Category:Sailors
